2026-03-01 20:28:50,027 472725 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 7, 'text': '## Cache Design\n\n### What to cache (per page, per map rule)\n- **result**: CONFIRMED / ERROR / GAP / NOT_RELEVANT\n- **detail**: what was found or missing\n- **source_hash**: hash of EUI+DUI files at validation time\n- **map_hash**: hash of the specific map rule at validation time\n\n### Cache invalidation triggers\n- Source file changed (EUI or DUI pug/js/json) → re-validate that page only\n- Map rule changed (match/action/dui fields) → re-validate that rule against all pages\n- New map rule added → validate against all pages (but only the new rule)\n- New page added → validate all rules against that page only\n\n### Where to store\nIn `docs/dui/reference-files.yaml` under each page\'s `validation` section:\n```yaml\nvalidation:\n  cache:\n    easyui_prefix_strip: { result: CONFIRMED, hash: "abc123" }\n    eui_date: { result: CONFIRMED, hash: "def456" }\n  source_hashes:\n    eui_pug: "hash"\n    eui_js: "hash"\n    dui_pug: "hash"\n    dui_js: "hash"\n  map_version: "hash of full map"\n```\n\n### Run flow\n1. Read register + map\n2. Compute current hashes for each page\'s source files\n3. Compare to cached hashes — build list of (page, rule) pairs that need re-validation\n4. Only read source files for pages that need re-validation\n5. Only check rules that changed or have no cached result\n6. Update cache with new results\n\n### Expected savings\n- First run: same as now (~100k tokens)\n- Subsequent runs with no changes: ~5k tokens (just reads register + map, compares hashes)\n- Subsequent runs with 1 page changed: ~15-20k tokens (reads that page\'s files + checks all rules)\n- Subsequent runs with 1 map rule changed: ~15-20k tokens (checks that rule across all pages)'}
