2026-03-02 14:07:18,283 497632 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'Page-prefix JSON lookup — mixin tries datagrid.<page>_<dgId>.json first, falls back to datagrid.<dgId>.json', 'description': "**Problem:** JSON configs are named `datagrid.<dgId>.json` where `<dgId>` is the HTML element ID. Different pages can use the same element ID (e.g. `#lines` in both physical_count and wip_count), causing them to share a single JSON config with wrong columns.\n\n**Fix:** Change the datagrid mixin's JSON lookup to try page-prefixed filename first:\n1. Derive page name from template path (already available in pug render context)\n2. Try `fn.pug.jsonRead('datagrid.' + pageName + '_' + dgId)` first\n3. Fall back to `fn.pug.jsonRead('datagrid.' + dgId)` for backward compatibility\n\n**Files to change:**\n- `html/dui/mixins/datagrid.pug` — the `jsonRead` call (currently line ~8)\n- `lib/helpers.js` — verify `jsonRead` resolution path, may need to check how page name is available\n\n**What stays the same:**\n- HTML element IDs unchanged (`#lines` stays `#lines`)\n- Page JS unchanged (`$('#lines')` stays)\n- Existing JSON files with bare `<dgId>` names continue to work (fallback)\n\n**What changes going forward:**\n- New JSON configs use `datagrid.<page>_<dgId>.json` convention\n- Colliding IDs get page-prefixed JSON files"}
2026-03-02 14:07:27,892 497632 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'One-shot fix — rename colliding JSON configs + clean up orphans', 'description': '**After step 14 (mixin change) is working:**\n\n**Rename collisions:**\n- `inv/json/datagrid.lines.json` → `inv/json/datagrid.physical_count_lines.json` (physical_count page)\n- Create `inv/json/datagrid.wip_count_lines.json` with correct wip_count columns (from EUI JS)\n\n**Verify and clean orphans:**\n- `inv/json/datagrid.cpfiles.json` — check if used by +filegrid#cpfiles in cp_man\n- `inv/json/datagrid.pofiles.json` — check if used by +filegrid in purchase pages\n- `inv/json/datagrid.pth.json` — check if used by any page\n- `sales/json/datagrid.qfiles.json` — check if used by +filegrid#qfiles in quote_man\n- `vwltsa/json/datagrid.table#data.json` — invalid filename with # char, delete\n\n**For each orphan:** grep all pug files for the ID. If truly unreferenced, delete. If referenced by +filegrid, keep (filegrid uses same jsonRead path).\n\n**Do NOT touch the 12 missing configs** — those are unmigrated pages, not a cleanup issue.'}
2026-03-02 14:07:39,413 497632 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'Update migration map + /dui-migrate skill with page-prefix JSON naming convention', 'description': '**After steps 14-15 are done:**\n\n**Migration map updates:**\n- `columns_inline` entry: update notes to say JSON filename is `datagrid.<page>_<dgId>.json`\n- `datagrid_column_editors` entry: same\n- `json_formatter_extraction` entry: same\n- `datagrid_manual_editor` entry: same\n- Add new entry `json_config_naming` documenting the convention and collision risk\n\n**Skill updates:**\n- `/dui-migrate` SKILL.md Phase 3 step 15: currently says "Write to html/dui/mod/<module>/json/datagrid.<dgId>.json" — change to `datagrid.<page>_<dgId>.json`\n- `/dui-state` SKILL.md Step 1: currently globs `datagrid.*.json` — update to note page-prefix convention\n- `/dui-learn` SKILL.md: register schema `json_configs` field uses bare IDs — update examples\n\n**Convention rule (add to map):**\n```yaml\njson_config_naming:\n  match: "datagrid.<id>.json"\n  action: flag\n  notes: >\n    JSON config files use page-prefixed names: datagrid.<page>_<dgId>.json\n    The mixin tries page-prefixed first, falls back to bare <dgId>.\n    New migrations MUST use page prefix. Bare names only for unique IDs.\n    Example: physical_count page with #lines → datagrid.physical_count_lines.json\n```'}
