2026-03-02 14:45:17,994 497632 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'Rework /dui-learn — reference-mining approach starting with sa_parts', 'description': 'Rewrite SKILL.md to drop the scoring/caching/threshold machinery. New purpose: mine proven working pages for conversion patterns. Read EUI+DUI pairs, classify every transform, check against migration map, report gaps/conflicts/confirmations. Start with sa_parts as the single reference page to validate the logic.'}
2026-03-02 15:01:33,708 497632 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'text': '## Reworked /dui-learn approach\n\n### Purpose\nMine proven-working DUI pages to extract every EUI→DUI transform, cross-reference against migration map. Three outputs:\n1. **Proven** — rule exists, page confirms it → add page to `found_on`\n2. **Gap** — page did a transform with no rule → add new rule\n3. **Wrong** — rule exists but page did something different → flag for correction\n\n### Procedure\n```\n/dui-learn <page>\n1. Read migration map\n2. Read EUI pug + JS\n3. Read DUI pug + JS + JSON configs\n4. For each map rule: is it relevant to this page?\n   - YES + DUI matches → PROVEN (add page to found_on)\n   - YES + DUI differs → WRONG (report conflict)\n   - NOT RELEVANT → skip\n5. For each EUI→DUI difference not covered by any rule → GAP\n6. Report: N proven, N wrong, N gaps\n7. User approves → update map (add found_on, add new rules, fix wrong rules)\n```\n\n### What was dropped\n- No scoring / /dui-state calls\n- No hash caching\n- No 80% threshold\n- No batch processing\n- No register metadata management\n- No reference-files.yaml (or simplified to just a page list)\n\n### sa_parts dry run results\n- 33 confirmed (map rule matches page)\n- 2 incomplete (JSON converted, JS not — eui.date, eui.currency)\n- 1 error (console.warn still present, map says strip)\n- 8 gaps (new rules needed: page_ready_wrapper, hide→hidden, filebox, modal cleanup, fragment prefix, jQuery Mobile classes, frm2dic, easyui-linkbutton CSS)\n- 4 shim-dependent (butEn, linkbutton, tbar.dgre_, .window)\n\n### Map changes: `found_on` field\nEach rule gets `found_on: [page1, page2, ...]` stamped when proven against a reference page.\n\n### Expected coverage\n- sa_parts alone: ~47% of rules proven\n- + purchase_manager + contact_man: ~70% proven\n- After 3-4 pages: diminishing returns, map essentially complete'}
