2026-03-02 16:14:12,180 497632 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'text': '## Scope\n\nFull audit and update of ALL component documentation in `docs/dui/*.md` to reflect current state of mixins, plugins, and APIs. This includes:\n\n1. **Update all existing docs** — every tab (Overview, Mixins, Parameters, Examples, Output, JS API, Notes) for all 16 existing doc files\n2. **Add missing docs** — create new `.md` files for mixins/plugins that have no documentation yet\n3. **Verify every example uses mixins** — ABSOLUTE RULE: if a mixin exists for it, the example MUST use the mixin. No raw HTML/DaisyUI classes where `+modal()`, `+button()`, `+form()`, `+fitem()`, `+datagrid()`, `+tabs()`, etc. exist\n\n## What needs updating (since ~Feb 24)\n\nMust read every mixin file and plugin file to identify what changed. Key areas:\n- Modal plugin/mixin — major rework happened\n- Tree component — new plugin + mixin added\n- Datagrid — toolbar JSON config, asdpx, editors\n- Form — form-plugin state machine\n- Input — fitem, combobox, datebox, qbe types\n- Button — actions.pug `+button` replaced `+linkbutton`\n- Layout — vsplit/hsplit/panel\n\n## Gaps — mixins with no doc file\n\n- `feedback.pug` — alert/toast/messager patterns\n- `display.pug` — display-only components  \n- `print.pug` — print mixins\n- `actions.pug` — may be covered by button.md but needs verification\n- `nav.pug` — partially covered by tabs.md and menu.md\n- `layout.pug` — partially covered by split-panel.md\n\n## Gaps — plugins with no doc file\n\n- qbe-plugin, combobox-plugin, datebox-plugin, ajax-plugin, page-plugin, panel-plugin, dataloader-plugin, dynadd-plugin, print-plugin, worker-plugin, misc-plugin\n\n## Rules\n\n- **Mixin-first examples** — NEVER use raw HTML where a mixin exists. No `<dialog class="modal">`, use `+modal()`. No `<button class="btn">`, use `+button()`. No `<div class="form-control">`, use `+fitem()`.\n- Read current mixin source before writing any doc — the mixin signature IS the truth\n- Read current plugin source before writing JS API section — the plugin IS the truth\n- Parameters table must match actual mixin arguments (read the pug source)\n- Output section shows what HTML the mixin actually generates (render mentally or check browser)\n\n## Procedure\n\n1. Read each mixin file to catalog current signatures and features\n2. Read each plugin file to catalog current JS API\n3. For each existing doc: compare against source, update every stale section\n4. For each gap: create new doc following standard tab format\n5. Verify examples use mixins throughout — fix any raw HTML violations\n6. Test in browser — load help page, select each component, verify rendering'}
2026-03-02 16:18:19,684 497632 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 9, 'text': "## Mixin Catalog Summary (from source audit)\n\n### PRIMARY DUI components (need docs):\n**actions.pug:** +button, +menubutton\n**form.pug:** +form, +fieldset, +fitem, +label, +hint, +validator\n**input.pug:** +input, +combobox, +textbox, +datebox, +numberbox, +numberspinner, +timespinner, +spinner, +searchbox, +passwordbox, +filebox, +qbe, +qbemodal, +spec, +combo\n**layout.pug:** +vsplit, +hsplit, +panel, +layout, +divider, +drawer, +footer, +hero, +stack\n**datagrid.pug:** +datagrid (single mixin, huge scope — JSON config, toolbar, editors, asdpx)\n**nav.pug:** +tabs, +tab-item, +menuItem\n**toolbar.pug:** +toolbar and 9 sub-sections (toolbar-nav, toolbar-actions, toolbar-output, etc.)\n**feedback.pug:** +modal, +modal-footer\n**group.pug:** +card, +card_body, +card_actions, +indicator, +indicator_item, +join, +list, +list_row\n**tree.pug:** +tree, +tree-node, +tree-render\n**print.pug:** +print-modals\n**visual.pug:** +mockup_browser, +mockup_code, +mockup_phone, +mockup_window, +code_line\n\n### EUI ALIASES (mention in parent doc, NOT own doc):\n- +linkbutton → alias for +button (actions.pug)\n- +dialog → alias for +modal (feedback.pug)\n- +window → alias for +modal (feedback.pug)\n- +region → alias for +panel (layout.pug)\n- +split → DEPRECATED, use +vsplit/+hsplit\n\n### LEGACY (do NOT document as components):\n- +script, +dwap (dev.pug) — no-ops kept for compat\n- +udfs, +udf (input.pug) — EUI legacy UDF fields\n\n### SKELETONS (do NOT document — not implemented):\n50+ skeleton mixins across display, interactive, visual, nav, feedback, input — just render placeholder divs\n\n### HELPERS/INTERNAL (do NOT document as components):\n- helpers.pug: getOpts(), resolveInputId(), detectInputType(), isBoolCombo(), surfaceDepth(), _state\n- utils.pug: +content, +section, +testOutput (test page only)\n\n## Doc file decisions\n\n### Existing docs to UPDATE (16):\noverview.md, page-lifecycle.md, tabs.md, menubutton.md, button.md, form.md, remember.md, datagrid.md, input.md, modal.md, toolbar.md, menu.md, split-panel.md, group.md, tree.md, maptable.md\n\n### NEW docs to CREATE:\n- print.md — print-modals system\n- visual.md — mockup components (if worth documenting)\n\n### Docs that may need MERGING/RENAMING:\n- split-panel.md covers layout.pug — should it become layout.md?\n- menu.md vs nav.pug — menuItem is in nav.pug\n\n### Components that DON'T need own doc:\n- toolbar (internal page chrome, not page-author-facing)\n- helpers (internal)\n- dev (legacy)\n- unknown (empty)", 'id': 564}
