2026-03-02 18:11:49,823 644894 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'note', 'text': '## Migration Protection — CSS Rules\n\n**ALL CSS in ulbar.css and sa_jobplan.css must be preserved during /dui-migrate.**\n\nThis page is NOT a standard form+datagrid. The datagrid IS the rendering engine for a Gantt-style scheduling board. Every CSS rule — including those targeting `.datagrid-cell`, `.datagrid-row`, `td[field]`, and `#job_planner tbody tr td` — styles the planning blocks, capacity indicators, and drag-drop targets.\n\n### Rules for /dui-migrate:\n1. Do NOT strip any CSS selectors that reference datagrid internals\n2. Do NOT convert hex color literals to theme variables — the different shades (#FAFAFA, #EEEEEE, #DDDDDD, #e6e6e6, #357ec7, #ccc, etc.) are deliberately distinct visual states\n3. The DUI CSS files at `html/dui/mod/vwltsa/css/` are ready to use — include them via `style: include css/ulbar.css` and `style: include css/sa_jobplan.css` in the DUI pug template\n4. The inline style block from the EUI pug (lines 95-152) has already been merged into sa_jobplan.css — do NOT duplicate it in the DUI pug template\n5. Image references (`../img/red-0.5.png` etc.) resolve to `/public/img/` and work in DUI without changes'}
