2026-03-02 19:01:58,721 649192 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 5, 'text': '## EUI vs DUI Datagrid Cell Structure Comparison\n\n### EUI Structure (from live browser inspection)\n\n**DOM hierarchy:**\n```\nTD[field="20260127"] (vertical-align: top, padding: 0)\n  └─ DIV.datagrid-cell.datagrid-cell-c4-20260127 \n       ├─ UL.ulbar.u0  (job bars for unit 0)\n       ├─ UL.ulbar.u1  (job bars for unit 1, if multi-unit)\n       └─ ...\n```\n\n**EUI base .datagrid-cell CSS (from easyui/themes/default/datagrid.css lines 99-111):**\n```css\n.datagrid-cell {\n  margin: 0;\n  padding: 0 4px;\n  white-space: nowrap;\n  word-wrap: normal;\n  overflow: hidden;\n  height: 18px;\n  line-height: 18px;\n  font-size: 12px;\n}\n```\n\n**sa_jobplan.css overrides (lines 113-123):**\n```css\ndiv.datagrid-cell {\n  border-width: 1px;\n  border-color: transparent;\n  border-style: solid;\n}\ndiv.datagrid-cell.capmax { border-color: blueviolet !important; }\ndiv.datagrid-cell.capex { border-color: var(--color-error) !important; }\ndiv.datagrid-cell.capdis { border-color: transparent !important; }\n```\n\n**EUI JS overrides (fixRowHeight):**\n- Sets `height: auto` on all .datagrid-cell divs so they expand to fit ulbar content\n- The `unp` column cell gets explicit pixel height matching the row height\n\n**Key computed values (live):**\n- Date cell: height=auto (computed 133px from content), overflow=hidden, padding=0, display=block, border=1px solid transparent\n- Unp cell: height=227px (set by fixRowHeight JS), overflow=hidden\n- Frozen rid cell: height=auto (computed 18px), overflow=hidden\n- TD: vertical-align=top, padding=0\n- Box-sizing: content-box\n\n**Header structure (EUI):**\n- TD[field] > DIV.datagrid-cell > SPAN > SPAN.dow_2 (contains "Tue 27 Jan")\n- EUI uses innerHTML to set header content — HTML renders correctly\n\n### DUI Structure (current)\n\n**DOM hierarchy:**\n```\nTD[data-field="20260127"] \n  └─ DIV.datagrid-cell\n       └─ (content set by formatter/loadData)\n```\n\n**Missing CSS:** DUI has ZERO .datagrid-cell CSS rules anywhere. The div exists but has no:\n- height (defaults to 0 when empty, collapses)\n- overflow\n- padding\n- display (defaults to block but no sizing)\n- border (sa_jobplan.css has rules but they need the base to work)\n\n**Header rendering (DUI):**\n- datagrid-plugin.js line 67: `th.textContent = col.title || \'\'`\n- textContent ESCAPES HTML — `<span class="dow_2">Tue 27 Jan</span>` shows as literal text\n- Must use `th.innerHTML` for HTML column titles\n\n### Fixes Needed\n\n1. **Add base .datagrid-cell CSS** — either global (components.css) or page-level (sa_jobplan.css)\n   - Minimum: `display: block; overflow: hidden; padding: 0;`\n   - Job planner needs `height: auto` (not 18px default) — cells expand to fit content\n   \n2. **Fix renderColumns** — `th.textContent` → `th.innerHTML` for HTML column titles\n\n3. **Fix sa_jobplan.css selectors:**\n   - `td[field="bar"]` → `td[data-field="bar"]` (line 26)\n   - `td[field="bar"] ul > li` → `td[data-field="bar"] ul > li` (line 31)\n   - `tr.datagrid-header-row td > div > span` → different (DUI uses th, not td>div) (line 48)\n   - `.datagrid-row-over` → `.hover` (DaisyUI class, line 207)\n   - `[field=unp]` → `[data-field=unp]` (in fixheight JS, line 231)\n\n4. **Fix load() function EUI selectors:**\n   - `.datagrid-view1 table tbody tr.datagrid-row[datagrid-row-index=N]` → find by _rowIndex\n   - `.datagrid-view2 table tbody tr.datagrid-row[datagrid-row-index=N]` → same row (single table)\n   - `td[field=X]` → `td[data-field=X]`\n   - `tr.datagrid-row` → `tbody tr`\n\n5. **Fix jobshow() function:**\n   - `tbody tr[datagrid-row-index]` → `#jplandg tbody tr`\n   - `tr.datagrid-row[datagrid-row-index]` → `tr` with _rowIndex check\n   - `.datagrid-view1 tr.datagrid-row[datagrid-row-index]` → same\n\n6. **Fix ddrop() function:**\n   - `.datagrid-view2 .datagrid-btable .datagrid-row td[field]` → `#jplandg tbody tr td[data-field]`\n\n7. **Fix fwd/bak scroll:**\n   - `.datagrid-view2 .datagrid-header .datagrid-header-row td:first-child .datagrid-cell` → need DUI equivalent for column width\n   - `$(\'#jplandg\').data(\'datagrid\').dc.body2` → DUI scroll container is the `.overflow-auto` wrapper'}
