2026-03-02 20:46:26,558 665862 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 5, 'text': "## DUI vs EUI Datagrid Architecture — Key for JS Fixes\n\n**EUI: Dual-table split view**\n- `.datagrid-view1` = frozen columns (left table)\n- `.datagrid-view2` = scrollable columns (right table)\n- Same row exists in BOTH tables, linked by `datagrid-row-index` HTML attribute\n- `tr.datagrid-row[datagrid-row-index=N]` selects a row by index\n- `td[field=X]` selects a cell by field name\n\n**DUI: Single table**\n- ONE `<table>` inside `#jplandg` — no view1/view2 split\n- Rows have `_rowIndex` as a JS DOM property (NOT an HTML attribute)\n- `td[data-field=X]` selects a cell (uses `data-` prefix)\n- No `.datagrid-row` class — just `tbody tr`\n\n**Migration pattern:**\n- `$('.datagrid-view1 ... tr.datagrid-row[datagrid-row-index=N]')` → `$('#jplandg tbody tr').filter(function(){ return this._rowIndex === N })`\n- `$('.datagrid-view2 ... tr.datagrid-row[datagrid-row-index=N]')` → same row (single table)\n- `td[field=X]` → `td[data-field=X]`\n- `.attr('field')` → `.attr('data-field')`\n- `tr.datagrid-row` → `#jplandg tbody tr`\n- `[datagrid-row-index]` attribute → filter by `_rowIndex` property"}
