2026-03-02 21:21:39,967 665862 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'Investigate frozen column CSS issues', 'description': "Two issues when applying position:sticky to first 3 columns of #jplandg:\n1. TRANSPARENT BACKGROUND — frozen columns don't occlude scrolled content behind them\n2. WIDTH DESTRUCTION — column widths collapse/change from JSON-specified values (100/50/132px)\n\nMust find root cause for both before attempting any fix. CSS-only approach (no JS)."}
2026-03-02 21:21:48,773 665862 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'text': "Investigation plan:\n1. Check what the actual DOM structure is — table, scroll container, class list on `<table>`\n2. Check what DaisyUI `.table` class does to td backgrounds (does it set transparent?)\n3. Check what the computed background-color is on a td right now (no sticky)\n4. Check if `border-collapse: separate` (line 3 of sa_jobplan.css) vs `collapse` matters for sticky\n5. Check how the datagrid plugin sets column widths — `<col>` elements? inline styles? th width attrs?\n6. Determine if sticky itself is causing the width change, or if it's a side-effect of something else\n\nKey constraint: CSS-only solution, no JS for frozen columns."}
2026-03-02 21:22:53,679 665862 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'text': "## Investigation Findings\n\n### Issue 1: TRANSPARENT BACKGROUND\n\n**Root cause**: Every element in the rendering chain — `td`, `tr`, `th`, `table` — has `background-color: rgba(0,0,0,0)` (transparent). The visible white background users see comes from the **scroll container** `#jplandg` div which has class `bg-base-100` → `oklch(1 0 0)`.\n\nWhen `position: sticky` is applied to a td, the td stays in place but is still transparent — scrolled content behind it is visible through it.\n\n**Fix**: Any sticky cell MUST have an explicit opaque `background-color` set. `var(--color-base-100)` is correct. The previous attempts DID set this, but may have been fighting specificity with DaisyUI. Need to verify `!important` beats DaisyUI `.table` rules.\n\nDaisyUI already solves this for `table-pin-rows` (line 2330 in main.css): it sets `background-color: var(--color-base-100)` on thead tr. And for `table-pin-cols` (line 2342): it sets same on `tr th`. We need the same for `tr td` on frozen columns.\n\n### Issue 2: WIDTH DESTRUCTION\n\n**Root cause**: NOT caused by position:sticky itself. The widths are ALREADY wrong before sticky is applied:\n- 32 columns, total configured width: 3362px, total actual width: 3173px\n- `table-layout: auto` + `w-full` class on table\n- Browser auto-layout shrinks ALL columns proportionally to fit — rid: 100→84, units: 50→40, unp: 132→124\n- Date columns GROW slightly: 110→113-117 (content-driven)\n\nThe table is wider than the container (3180px vs 1556px) so w-full isn't constraining it. The shrinking is auto-layout redistributing widths based on content.\n\n**Fix options**:\na) `min-width` on frozen columns to prevent shrinking (simple, targeted)\nb) Remove `w-full` class from table (may have side effects)\nc) `table-layout: fixed` (forces all columns to specified widths, may break date column auto-sizing)\n\nOption (a) is safest — only affects the 3 frozen columns, leaves everything else alone.\n\n### Left offset calculation\nWith min-width enforced:\n- col 0 (rid): min-width: 100px → left: 0\n- col 1 (units): min-width: 50px → left: 100px\n- col 2 (unp): min-width: 132px → left: 150px\n- Border-right 2px on col 2 → total frozen width: 284px", 'id': 573}
2026-03-02 21:26:12,362 665862 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'text': "## Confirmed Fix\nTwo CSS rules per frozen column:\n1. `background-color: var(--color-base-100)` — opaque theme-friendly background (td cells are transparent by default, white comes from scroll container)\n2. `min-width` matching JSON width (100/50/132px) — prevents table-layout:auto from shrinking, makes left offsets (0/100/150) correct\n\nIf either doesn't work, revert before trying anything else."}
