2026-03-02 21:59:45,812 665862 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_new args={'name': 'datagrid-frozen-cols', 'title': 'Add frozen column support to datagrid plugin', 'steps': ['Investigate current datagrid plugin column rendering', 'Design frozen column API and CSS generation', 'Implement frozen column support in datagrid-plugin.js', 'Update sa_jobplan JSON config to use frozen:true', 'Remove page-specific frozen CSS from sa_jobplan.css', 'Verify on job planner page', 'Test on a second datagrid to confirm reusability']}
2026-03-02 21:59:54,027 665862 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'goal', 'text': 'Make frozen (sticky) columns a universal datagrid feature. Any datagrid can freeze leading columns by adding `"frozen": true` to column definitions in JSON config. The plugin handles all CSS (sticky positioning, left offsets, opaque backgrounds, z-index layering, min-width). No page-specific CSS needed.'}
2026-03-02 22:00:09,902 665862 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': '## Approach\n\n### JSON API\nColumn def gets `"frozen": true`:\n```json\n{ "field": "rid", "title": "Resource ID", "width": 100, "frozen": true }\n```\nFrozen columns must be contiguous leading columns (left side).\n\n### Plugin implementation (datagrid-plugin.js)\nAfter table is built and columns rendered:\n1. Read column defs, identify frozen columns\n2. Compute cumulative `left` offsets from column widths\n3. Apply to both `th[data-field]` and `td[data-field]` for each frozen column:\n   - `position: sticky`\n   - `left: <cumulative>px`\n   - `z-index: 2` (body), `3` (header), `4` (corner = frozen+header)\n   - `min-width: <width>px`\n4. Apply `background-color: var(--color-base-100)` to all tbody td in the table\n5. Apply `background-color: var(--color-base-200)` to thead th (header row sticky top:0)\n6. Add `border-right: 2px solid var(--color-base-300)` to the last frozen column\n7. Ensure `border-collapse: separate; border-spacing: 0` on the table\n\n### What moves out of sa_jobplan.css\nAll frozen column CSS currently in sa_jobplan.css gets removed. The `background-color: var(--color-base-100)` on tbody td may stay if needed for other reasons.\n\n### Lessons from investigation\n- Hidden columns exist in DOM with `display:none` — nth-child selectors fail, must use `data-field`\n- td/tr/th/table are all transparent by default — sticky cells MUST have explicit opaque bg\n- `table-layout: auto` shrinks columns — `min-width` prevents this\n- `border-collapse: collapse` breaks sticky — must use `separate`'}
