2026-03-02 23:12:39,789 665862 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 13, 'text': 'APPROACH: Cannot use +menubutton mixin — it wraps a .dropdown with a trigger button, but context menus have no button anchor. They appear at cursor position on right-click.\n\nUse a standalone ul.menu (DaisyUI menu component) rendered in pug, hidden by default (display:none), positioned via JS at e.pageX/e.pageY on right-click with position:fixed.\n\nPUG changes:\n- Replace #opnmenu.easyui-menu with ul#opnmenu.menu.bg-base-100.shadow-lg.rounded-box\n- Menu items as li > a(data-name="xxx") preserving all existing name values\n- Conditional planplus block for lock/unlock vs move up/down variants\n- Separator via DaisyUI menu divider (li > hr or empty li with border)\n\nJS changes (3 areas):\n1. Right-click handler (~line 362): Replace $(\'#opnmenu\').menu(\'show\',{left,top}) with:\n   - Set #opnmenu css left/top to e.pageX/e.pageY, display:block\n   - Store src element reference on the menu (e.g. data attribute or variable)\n\n2. onShow logic (~line 771): Replace .menu(\'enableItem\')/.menu(\'disableItem\') with:\n   - Toggle CSS classes (pointer-events-none opacity-30) on li elements\n   - Find items by data-name attribute instead of .menu(\'findItem\',\'text\')\n\n3. onClick routing (~line 792): Replace .menu({onClick}) with:\n   - Delegated click handler on #opnmenu: read data-name from clicked a, run same switch/case\n   - Hide menu after click (display:none)\n\n4. Dismiss: Add document click handler to hide menu when clicking outside\n\nExisting action handlers (open, up, down, uplan, focus, hilite, lock, unlock) stay UNTOUCHED.'}
