2026-03-03 08:26:34,881 665862 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'task': 'datagrid', 'title': 'Toolbar button toggle — scope CRUD disable to owned buttons only', 'description': 'The datagrid plugin disables ALL toolbar buttons on init/clearSelections/deselect, then enables ALL on row select. This catches custom action buttons (Priorities, AutoPlan, Apply, scroll arrows) that should always be enabled. Current workaround: `data-always-enabled` attribute + `alwaysEnabled` JSON property on per-button basis. Correct fix: a datagrid-level boolean property (e.g. `tbarCrud: true`) that tells the plugin to only toggle its own CRUD buttons (`_add`, `_edit`, `_del`) rather than every button in the toolbar.'}
