2026-03-03 08:27:04,807 665862 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 18, 'text': 'CONTEXT: Discovered during migrate-jobplan step 7 (toolbar migration).\n\nCURRENT BEHAVIOR (datagrid-plugin.js):\n- Line 168: `var DIS_CLS = \'opacity-40 pointer-events-none\'`\n- Line 419 (row deselect): `$(state._toolbar).find(\'button:not([data-always-enabled])\').each(tbarDisable)`\n- Line 436 (row select): `$(state._toolbar).find(\'button:not([data-always-enabled])\').each(tbarEnable)`\n- Line 704 (clearSelections): same blanket disable\n- Line 193: `_btnAdd` explicitly enabled on init\n\nDESIGN REASON: On load with no row selected, only Add should be enabled. Edit/Delete need a selected row. This is correct for CRUD lifecycle but implemented as "disable everything" rather than "disable only CRUD buttons."\n\nWORKAROUND IN PLACE:\n- datagrid.pug mixin: `alwaysEnabled` JSON property → renders `data-always-enabled` attribute\n- Pages: sa_jobplan uses this on Priorities, AutoPlan, Apply, scroll arrows, Stats\n- Plugin already has the selector `button:not([data-always-enabled])` so it works\n\nPROPOSED FIX:\n- New datagrid JSON boolean property (name TBD — `tbarCrud`?)\n- When true: plugin only toggles `state._btnAdd`, `state._btnEdit`, `state._btnDel`\n- When false/omitted: current behavior (toggle all) — preserves backward compat\n- Once implemented, `alwaysEnabled` / `data-always-enabled` can be removed from jobplan/jobsched\n- Need to audit all datagrid JSON configs to decide if default should flip'}
