2026-03-03 08:28:53,447 665862 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'goal', 'id': 500, 'text': 'Migrate vwltsa/sa_jobsched (Job Schedule) from EUI to DUI.\n\nSimilar to sa_jobplan but SIMPLER — a read-only Gantt chart showing jobs × 30-day horizon. Operation bars rendered as absolutely-positioned `<div class="ibar">` inside cells (not `<ul>/<li>` like jobplan). No drag & drop, no planplus, no priorities window.\n\n## Page characteristics\n\n1. **ALL CSS is functional** — ibar positioning, arrow indicators, bar colors, weekend overlay. Currently inline in pug, needs extraction.\n2. **No datagrid JSON exists** — columns defined entirely in JS (frozenColumns array + dynamic sched column). Needs JSON creation.\n3. **No form fields, no standard lifecycle** — filtering via 3 comboboxes (Customer, Job Class, Filter By). No Add/Save/Delete.\n4. **Auto-load page** — datagrid fetches data from `vwltsa^sa_jobsched` on ready.\n5. **EUI datagrid is the rendering engine** — frozen left columns (Job Ref, PRI, Cust ID, Part ID, SO, Job Class, dates, 10 UDF fields) + 1 wide `sched` column with operation bars.\n6. **EUI-specific APIs**: `.menu(\'show\')`, `.panel()`, `.combobox()` — each needs DUI replacement.\n7. **Namespace was mis-migrated** — `dwap.` → `$.dui.` which is wrong. Needs `$.page.fn.*`.\n8. **551 lines of JS** — ~15 functions, all client-side display logic.\n9. **Context menu** — simple, only "View Job" (1 item vs 8 in jobplan).\n10. **Row expand** — clicking a bar cell expands row to show overlapping operations vertically.\n11. **Dynamic UDF field labels** — frozen column titles updated from `$.dui.pdata.udfid` at runtime.\n\n## Lessons from sa_jobplan (MUST FOLLOW)\n\n- **Investigate root cause before fixing** — no patching on patches\n- **Use data-field attribute selectors** for frozen columns (NOT nth-child — hidden columns break it)\n- **Set tbody td background to base-100** explicitly — all elements are transparent by default, sticky columns bleed\n- **Verify with screenshots and DOM inspection** — never claim something works without proof\n- **Use the datagrid mixin toolbar system** — do NOT just move/rename the toolbar div\n- **Check live EUI (/dui-pure3d)** before declaring features dead or working\n- **Two attempt limit** on any fix — after 2 failures, stop and diagnose\n\n### Toolbar migration (proven on jobplan step 7)\n- Comboboxes → JSON `toolbar` array as `type:\'field\'` items (rendered as +fitem, left-aligned)\n- Action buttons → JSON `toolbar` array as button items with `alwaysEnabled: true` (rendered as +button, right-aligned)\n- Non-standard items (excel link, scroll arrows, conditional buttons) → pug `block` content with `data-always-enabled` attribute\n- `.linkbutton({onClick})` → `.on(\'click\')` in JS\n- Remove old toolbar div and its CSS entirely\n- **`alwaysEnabled` / `data-always-enabled` is critical** — the datagrid plugin disables ALL toolbar buttons on init/deselect/clearSelections. Without this attribute, action buttons that should always be clickable get disabled. See datagrid task step 18 for the proper fix (tbarCrud property).'}
2026-03-03 08:29:10,134 665862 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'id': 501, 'text': '## EUI → DUI Component Map for sa_jobsched\n\n| EUI Component | DUI Equivalent | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `$(\'#el\').datagrid(...)` | DUI datagrid plugin | Same jQuery call pattern |\n| `$(\'#el\').combobox(...)` | DUI combobox plugin | Same jQuery call pattern |\n| `$(\'#el\').menu(\'show\',{left,top})` | DaisyUI `ul.menu` positioned via JS | Same pattern proven on jobplan step 13 |\n| `$(\'#el\').panel(...)` | DUI panel mixin | Already partially converted in pug |\n| `toolbar: \'#jstbar\'` | Datagrid mixin toolbar system | JSON toolbar config — see step 4 notes |\n| `dwap.page.*` | `$.page.fn.*` | Page-specific functions |\n| `dwap.bhave.*` | `$.dui.bhave.*` | Global behaviour |\n| `ajaxget()` | `ajaxget()` | Shimmed, same signature |\n| `newtab()` | `linkwin()` or DUI equivalent | Opens new tab for job view |\n| `isodate()` / `myDate()` | Shimmed via misc-plugin | Date formatting |\n| `.linkbutton({onClick})` | `.on(\'click\')` | No EUI linkbutton init needed — DUI buttons are plain HTML |\n\n## Toolbar migration approach (PROVEN on jobplan step 7)\n\n### How it works\nThe datagrid mixin toolbar (datagrid.pug line 44-98):\n- `toolbar` array in JSON config with `type:\'field\'` items (→ +fitem, left-aligned) and button items (→ +button, right-aligned)\n- `block` content in pug for arbitrary injection into toolbar\n- `#<dgId>_toolbar` ID convention — JS plugin auto-detects it\n- Mixin supports `alwaysEnabled: true` on button items → renders `data-always-enabled` attribute\n\n### For sa_jobsched (#jstbar → #jsched_toolbar)\nJSON toolbar:\n```json\n"toolbar": [\n  { "type": "field", "label": "Customer", "id": "cuscbo", "name": "cuscbo", "editor": { "type": "combobox" } },\n  { "type": "field", "label": "Job Class", "id": "woccbo", "name": "woccbo", "editor": { "type": "combobox" } },\n  { "type": "field", "label": "Filter By", "id": "filtercbo", "name": "filtercbo", "editor": { "type": "combobox" } }\n]\n```\nPug block content: Excel export (#dg2excel) with `data-always-enabled`\nRemove #jstbar div entirely + its CSS\nKeep .combobox({onSelect}) JS handlers — IDs preserved\n\n### CRITICAL: alwaysEnabled / data-always-enabled\nThe datagrid plugin disables ALL toolbar `<button>` elements on init/deselect/clearSelections (lines 419, 704). Any button that should always be clickable MUST have `data-always-enabled` attribute. Use `alwaysEnabled: true` in JSON for toolbar buttons, or `data-always-enabled` attribute in pug block content. Without this, buttons render faded and unclickable. See datagrid task step 18 for eventual proper fix.\n\n## Shared CSS with sa_jobplan\n\nAlready defined in sa_jobplan.css (reusable):\n- `.bg-red`, `.bg-grn`, `.bg-ora`, `.bg-blu`, `.bg-gry`, `.bg-sil`, `.bg-pur`, `.bg-cyn`, `.bg-yel`, `.bg-brn`, `.bg-clr`\n- `.bold`, `.center`, `.whtgry`\n- `.datagrid-cell` overrides in components.css\n\nsa_jobsched-specific CSS (needs own file):\n- `.ibar` positioning (absolute, percentage left/width)\n- `.arrow-up`, `.arrow-left`, `.arrow-right` (CSS triangle indicators)\n- `.opwr` (operation wrapper)\n- `.bar` td cell styling\n- `.wkend` weekend overlay\n- `.maxrun` excessive runtime highlight\n- `.status` progress background'}
2026-03-03 08:29:23,416 665862 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 4, 'text': "PROVEN PATTERN from jobplan step 7. Follow exactly.\n\nFILES TO CHANGE:\n1. JSON — create datagrid.sa_jobsched_jsched.json with toolbar array (3 combobox fields)\n2. PUG — remove #jstbar div, add block content to +datagrid#jsched for dg2excel with data-always-enabled\n3. JS — remove toolbar:'#jstbar' from datagrid init, convert any .linkbutton({onClick}) to .on('click')\n4. CSS — delete #jstbar CSS rules\n\nIMPLEMENTATION:\n- Comboboxes as JSON toolbar fields: type:'field', label, id, name, editor:{type:'combobox'}\n- No action buttons needed (jobsched has no Priorities/AutoPlan/Apply — only filter combos + excel)\n- Excel export via pug block content: `a#dg2excel.btn.btn-ghost.btn-xs(data-always-enabled)`\n- IDs MUST match existing JS references (#cuscbo, #woccbo, #filtercbo)\n\nGOTCHA: data-always-enabled\nThe datagrid plugin blanket-disables all toolbar buttons on init. Any non-CRUD button needs data-always-enabled attribute or it renders faded/unclickable. For JSON buttons use alwaysEnabled:true, for pug block content use data-always-enabled attribute directly."}
