2026-03-03 08:37:08,678 665862 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 11, 'text': 'SPECIAL INSTRUCTIONS FOR /dui-migrate ON sa_jobsched\n\nThese are lessons learned from the sa_jobplan migration that the skill MUST follow. The dumb regex migrator got ALL of these wrong on jobplan — do not repeat.\n\n## 1. NAMESPACE — $.page.fn.* (NOT $.dui.page.*)\nThe migrator\'s default `dwap.` → `$.dui.` is WRONG.\n- `dwap.page.*` → `$.page.fn.*` (page-specific functions)\n- `dwap.bhave.*` → `$.dui.bhave.*` (global behaviour — this one IS $.dui)\n- `dwap.pdata.*` → `$.dui.pdata.*` (page data from server)\n- Wrap all page code in `$.page.ready(function() { ... })`\n\n## 2. TOOLBAR — use datagrid mixin toolbar system\n- NEVER output `toolbar: \'#jstbar\'` — DUI datagrid plugin doesn\'t support selector-based toolbars\n- NEVER just move/rename the toolbar div\n- Comboboxes → JSON `toolbar` array as `type:\'field\'` items\n- Action buttons → JSON `toolbar` array as button items with `alwaysEnabled: true`\n- Non-standard items → pug `block` content inside +datagrid with `data-always-enabled`\n- Remove the old toolbar div (#jstbar) entirely\n\n## 3. CONTEXT MENU — DaisyUI ul.menu, NOT .easyui-menu\n- `ul#opnmenu.menu.menu-sm.bg-base-100.text-base-content.rounded-box.shadow-lg.p-2`\n- `style="position:fixed; z-index:9999; display:none; width:160px;"`\n- Items as `li: a(data-name="xxx")` — preserve all data-name values\n- Separators as `li: hr`\n- JS: position at `e.pageX/e.pageY`, show/hide via `.css({display:\'block\'/\'none\'})`\n- JS: delegated click handler on `#opnmenu a[data-name]`\n- JS: dismiss on document click outside\n\n## 4. BUTTONS — .on(\'click\'), NOT .linkbutton({onClick})\n- DUI buttons are plain HTML `<button>` — no JS init needed\n- Replace ALL `.linkbutton({onClick: fn})` with `.on(\'click\', fn)`\n- Replace `.linkbutton(\'enable\')` / `.linkbutton(\'disable\')` with class toggling\n\n## 5. DATAGRID SELECTORS — data-field, single table\nEUI uses dual tables (view1/view2) with `td[field=X]` and `tr.datagrid-row[datagrid-row-index=N]`.\nDUI is a single table:\n- `td[field=X]` → `td[data-field=X]`\n- `.attr(\'field\')` → `.attr(\'data-field\')`\n- `tr.datagrid-row` → `tbody tr`\n- `[datagrid-row-index=N]` → filter by `_rowIndex` JS property\n- `.datagrid-view1` / `.datagrid-view2` → just `#jsched` (single table)\n\n## 6. FROZEN COLUMNS — CSS sticky with data-field selectors\n- Use `[data-field="xxx"]` attribute selectors (NOT nth-child — hidden columns break it)\n- Every frozen td MUST have explicit `background-color: var(--color-base-100)` (transparent by default → bleed-through)\n- Use `min-width` matching JSON width to prevent table-layout:auto shrinkage\n- Header frozen cells need `z-index: 4` (above both sticky row and sticky column)\n\n## 7. CSS — extract inline, convert to theme variables\n- Extract ALL inline CSS from pug `style` blocks to `css/sa_jobsched.css`\n- Convert hex colors to `var(--color-*)` where appropriate\n- `.bg-red/.bg-grn` etc. are already defined in sa_jobplan.css — shared, don\'t duplicate\n- `.datagrid-cell` base CSS is in components.css — don\'t duplicate\n\n## 8. DATAGRID JSON — create the config file\n- File: `json/datagrid.sa_jobsched_jsched.json`\n- Include columns from the JS frozenColumns array as static columns\n- Include toolbar array with 3 combobox fields\n- Do NOT include dynamic date/sched columns — those are added by JS at runtime\n\n## 9. EUI APIs — replace or remove\n- `.panel()` → remove (DUI handles via mixin)\n- `.menu(\'show\')` → see context menu pattern above\n- `.combobox()` → DUI combobox plugin (same jQuery API)\n- `.tooltip()` → needs DUI equivalent or custom\n- `.window()` → DUI modal (if needed, unlikely for jobsched)\n- `.progressbar()` → native HTML or DaisyUI progress'}
