2026-03-03 10:46:08,814 757895 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': "**Architecture:**\n- Primary user works in the existing repo directory (no worktree) — zero migration\n- Additional users get worktrees created automatically on first interaction\n- Worktrees live under `<repo>/.worktrees/<username>/` with per-user branches\n- Each user's branch is named `mcpp/<username>` (e.g. `mcpp/alice`)\n\n**Schema changes:**\n- Add `worktree_path` column to `user_state` table (nullable — NULL = use project absolute_path)\n- Add `worktree_branch` column to `user_state` table\n\n**Config:**\n- Add `enable_worktrees: false` to workflow config (opt-in, off by default)\n\n**Key behaviors:**\n- `workspace_dir` resolution: check user_state.worktree_path first; if NULL, fall back to project.absolute_path\n- On first tool call from a non-primary user (when enable_worktrees=true): create worktree + branch automatically\n- `plan_checkpoint`/`plan_commit`: unchanged API, but operates on per-user worktree\n- `plan_push`: pushes user's branch to remote (not main)\n- New `plan_sync`: merges user branch into main (or rebases), handles conflicts gracefully\n- Worktree cleanup: `plan_task_complete` can optionally remove the worktree\n\n**Migration safety:**\n- enable_worktrees defaults to false — existing repos are untouched\n- If worktree_path is NULL, all git operations use project.absolute_path (identical to current behavior)\n- No schema migration required for existing data (new columns are nullable)"}
2026-03-03 10:48:02,780 757895 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_delete args={'number': 1}
2026-03-03 10:48:14,064 757895 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': "**Architecture:**\n- Primary user works in the existing repo directory (no worktree) — zero migration\n- Additional users get worktrees created automatically on first interaction\n- Worktree path is deterministic: `<repo>/.worktrees/<username>/` — nothing to store in DB\n- Each user's branch is named `mcpp/<username>` (e.g. `mcpp/alice`)\n\n**Config:**\n- Add `enable_worktrees: false` to workflow config defaults (opt-in)\n\n**Resolution logic (no schema changes):**\n1. enable_worktrees off? → use project.absolute_path (current behavior)\n2. Is this the repo owner / primary user? → use project.absolute_path\n3. Otherwise → `<absolute_path>/.worktrees/<username>/`, create if missing\n\n**Key behaviors:**\n- `plan_checkpoint`/`plan_commit`: unchanged API, operates on resolved workspace_dir\n- `plan_push`: pushes user's branch to remote\n- New `plan_sync`: merges user branch into main\n- Worktree creation: `git worktree add -b mcpp/<user> <path>` from main repo\n- Worktree cleanup: on task complete or explicit command"}
