2026-03-03 11:10:09,984 757895 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_new args={'name': 'worktree-hardening', 'title': 'Harden git worktree implementation — safety, edge cases, integration testing', 'steps': ['Fix add_all to exclude .worktrees from staging', 'Handle branch name collision in ensure_worktree', 'Handle stale worktree directory (exists on disk but not in git)', 'Handle worktree creation failure — clean up partial state', 'Add .git/info/exclude entry as belt-and-suspenders with pathspec', 'Write integration test: full cycle with bare remote (tmp_path only)', 'Write integration test: multi-user isolation verification', 'Write integration test: plan_sync merge and push', 'Write integration test: revert safety — one user revert does not affect others', 'Write integration test: edge cases — branch collision, stale dir, cleanup']}
2026-03-03 11:10:15,272 757895 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'goal', 'text': 'Make the worktree implementation production-safe. The current code has known edge cases that could corrupt repos or leak worktree contents into commits. Every failure mode must be handled gracefully, and the full lifecycle must be proven with integration tests using disposable tmp_path repos — never touching real repos.'}
2026-03-03 11:10:24,862 757895 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': "**Phase 1 — Fix known safety issues (steps 1-5):**\n1. `add_all()` uses `git add -A` which stages `.worktrees/` — fix with pathspec `:(exclude).worktrees`\n2. `ensure_worktree()` does `worktree add -b` which fails if branch already exists — detect and reuse\n3. Worktree dir could exist on disk from a previous crashed run but not be registered in git — detect and recover\n4. If `worktree add` fails partway, clean up the directory — don't leave partial state\n5. Write `.worktrees` to `.git/info/exclude` as secondary protection (pathspec is primary, this is belt-and-suspenders)\n\n**Phase 2 — Integration tests (steps 6-10):**\nAll tests use `tmp_path` with bare remote + cloned local. Simulate users via `USER` env var override.\n6. Full cycle: init → enable worktrees → checkpoint as user → push → verify\n7. Multi-user: alice and bob checkpoint independently, verify file isolation\n8. Sync: alice syncs to main, verify main has alice's files, bob unaffected\n9. Revert: root reverts own commit, verify alice/bob worktrees untouched\n10. Edge cases: branch exists, stale dir, creation failure recovery\n\n**Constraints:**\n- No raw git commands from the agent — all changes through code edits only\n- All testing via pytest with tmp_path — zero risk to real repos\n- Integration tests call mcpptool.execute() to test the full stack"}
