2026-03-03 14:07:05,285 783761 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'text': '## Problem with current implementation\n\n`_resolve_git_dir` silently redirects git operations to `.worktrees/<user>/` inside the repo, but Claude\'s file edits still go to the main project directory. The MCP server cannot control where the agent edits files — the agent\'s CWD is fixed by the client at launch time. The MCP protocol has no mechanism to change this (`roots` is read-only, client-to-server, no CWD concept).\n\nThis means git operations (commit, checkpoint) check the worktree (clean), while edits happen in the main dir. Result: "nothing to commit" even though changes exist.\n\nAdditionally, `enable_worktrees` in config.yaml is global to the mcpp-plan module — it applies to ALL projects, not per-project. Enabling it for testing affected mcpptest too, creating `.worktrees/root/` there.\n\n## Research findings\n\nEvery tool that does multi-user worktree isolation correctly handles it the same way: **the worktree IS the agent\'s working directory, set at launch time**.\n\n- **Claude Code** `--worktree` flag: creates worktree, launches agent with CWD = worktree path. Has `WorktreeCreate`/`WorktreeRemove` hooks for custom VCS.\n- **Cursor 2.0**: each background agent gets own worktree + isolated VM, CWD = worktree.\n- **parallel-code, ccswarm, ccmanager**: all create worktrees first, start agent processes inside them.\n\n## Correct approach: Claude Code WorktreeCreate/WorktreeRemove hooks\n\n1. mcpp-plan provides a `WorktreeCreate` hook script that:\n   - Reads the current repo path and username\n   - Creates a worktree (e.g. `<repo>/.worktrees/<user>/` or `/home/<user>/project/`) on branch `mcpp/<user>`\n   - Prints the absolute worktree path to stdout (required by Claude Code)\n2. Claude Code calls this hook before the session starts, sets agent CWD to the printed path\n3. Agent edits files in the worktree naturally — no redirection needed\n4. `workspace_dir` from MCP context IS the worktree, so git operations target the right place\n5. `WorktreeRemove` hook handles cleanup on session exit\n6. `plan_sync` merges user branch into main (this part of the current implementation is fine)\n\n## What needs to change\n\n- Remove `_resolve_git_dir` redirection logic — replace with plain `workspace_dir` passthrough\n- Remove `ensure_worktree` calls from git operation handlers\n- Keep worktree creation/removal functions in git.py — they\'ll be used by the hook scripts\n- Add hook scripts (WorktreeCreate, WorktreeRemove) that Claude Code can call\n- Keep `plan_sync` for merging user branches into main\n- Document the setup: user adds hooks to `.claude/settings.json`'}
