2026-03-03 15:18:37,316 807513 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'goal', 'text': 'Migrate vwltsa/sa_jobman (Job Manager) from EUI to DUI using the /dui-migrate skill.\n\nThis is one of the most complex pages in the system:\n- West-center split layout with WO tree in west panel\n- 3 nested form contexts (Job/Master, Sub Assembly, Operation) with different tab sets per context\n- Tree widget with custom formatters (progress bars, colored SEQ numbers, NCR flags, open-parts icons)\n- 6 custom toolbar buttons (Job Clone, Import Sub Assy, Job Export, Job Import, Print Traveller, Open NCR)\n- 18 SQL endpoints\n- Cookie-based filter state persistence\n- Multiple dialog windows (Clone, Import, GRL, OpCls, AddSub)\n- 3 include panels (wo_bas_inc, wo_sub_inc, wo_seq_inc)\n- Extensive page-specific CSS for tree decoration, status filters, job class panel\n\nCRITICAL: Page-specific stylesheets and associated classes MUST be preserved through migration.\nThe /dui-migrate skill should convert all components to standard DUI mixins (+hsplit, +vsplit, +tabs, +form, +combobox, etc.) but the custom CSS blocks that style the tree nodes, status toggles, and other page-unique elements must be kept intact.'}
2026-03-03 15:18:48,488 807513 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': '## Migration Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Discovery (Step 1)\n- Extract all inline CSS from EUI sa_jobman.pug (style blocks)\n- Catalog every CSS class used for tree decoration, status filters, job class panel\n- Identify which classes are page-specific vs EUI framework classes\n- Document the JS-generated classes (addClass calls in sa_jobman.js)\n\n### Phase 2: Migration with /dui-migrate\n- Run /dui-migrate on sa_jobman.pug\n- The skill converts EUI components → DUI mixins (layout, tabs, forms, combobox, etc.)\n- Page-specific `style` blocks and their associated CSS classes must be PRESERVED verbatim\n- The migrator must NOT strip or rename classes referenced by the preserved CSS\n\n### Phase 3: Include panels\n- Migrate wo_bas_inc.pug, wo_sub_inc.pug, wo_seq_inc.pug separately\n- Each has its own tab set and form fields\n\n### Phase 4: JS migration\n- sa_jobman.js: dwap → $.dui/$.page namespace changes\n- Tree widget API calls need DUI tree plugin equivalents\n- toolbar custom buttons → DUI toolbar integration\n\n### Dependencies\n- Task 205 (tree-component) — DUI tree plugin must exist\n- Task 204 (toolbut-container) — custom toolbar buttons need container'}
