2026-03-03 15:21:15,972 807513 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': "## Migration Plan (informed by migrate-jobplan patterns)\n\n### Phase 1: CSS Discovery & Extraction (Step 1)\n- Read EUI sa_jobman.pug inline style blocks — catalog every rule\n- Read sa_jobman.js — catalog every addClass/css/style class applied dynamically\n- Check for separate CSS files in html/eui/vwltsa/css/\n- Classify: tree-decoration vs filter-panel vs structural vs EUI-framework\n- Output: complete class inventory with which source defines and which source consumes each class\n\n### Phase 2: Create DUI CSS file\n- Extract all page-specific CSS into `html/dui/mod/vwltsa/css/sa_jobman.css`\n- Include via `style: include css/sa_jobman.css` in the DUI pug template\n- Do NOT duplicate inline — single source of truth in the CSS file\n- Keep hex colors where they represent distinct visual states (per jobplan precedent)\n\n### Phase 3: Write migration protection note\n- Explicit rules for /dui-migrate about what NOT to touch\n- ALL tree decoration CSS must be preserved\n- Class names referenced by JS formatters must NOT be renamed\n- Image references for tree icons must be preserved\n\n### Phase 4: Run /dui-migrate\n- Converts layout, tabs, forms, inputs → DUI mixins (+hsplit, +vsplit, +tabs, +form, +combobox, etc.)\n- Preserves page-specific style blocks and associated classes\n- sa_jobman.pug is the main page; wo_bas_inc, wo_sub_inc, wo_seq_inc are separate migrations\n\n### Phase 5: JS migration\n- dwap.page → $.page.fn, dwap.pdata → $.dui.pdata, etc.\n- Tree widget: EUI .tree() API → DUI tree-plugin (task 205)\n- Custom toolbar buttons: toolbut() → DUI #toolbut container (task 204)\n- Context menus: .menu('show') → DaisyUI positioned menu (same pattern as jobplan step 13)\n- Dialogs: .dialog()/.window() → DaisyUI modal + showModal()\n\n### Phase 6: Include panels (separate migrations)\n- wo_bas_inc.pug — Master tab with 8 inner tabs (Main, Dates, Costing, Engineering, Attachments, User Fields, Specs, Quality)\n- wo_sub_inc.pug — Sub Assembly tab\n- wo_seq_inc.pug — Operation tab with 8 inner tabs (Main, Setup/Run, Costing, User Fields, Specifications, Parts, Quality, Gauge)\n\n### EUI → DUI Component Map (from jobplan precedent)\n\n| EUI Component | DUI Equivalent | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `.easyui-layout` region west/center | `+hsplit` or `+layout` | West-center split |\n| `.easyui-tabs` | `+tabs` | Both outer #woform and inner #bastabs |\n| `.easyui-combobox` | `+combobox` | #wosel, #classid, form fields |\n| `.easyui-textbox` | `+textbox` | Form fields |\n| `.easyui-numberbox` | `+numberbox` | Qty/cost fields |\n| `.easyui-datebox` | `+datebox` | Date fields |\n| `.easyui-linkbutton` | `+button` or `+linkbutton` | Status toggles, action buttons |\n| `.easyui-tree` | DUI tree-plugin (task 205) | WO tree with custom formatters |\n| `.easyui-menu` | DaisyUI positioned menu | Context menus (#trmenu, #addmenu, #closejobmenu) |\n| `.easyui-dialog` / `.easyui-window` | DaisyUI `dialog` + `showModal()` | #cloneopt, #opncls, #importopt, #grl, #addsub |\n| `$.fn.panel('refresh', url)` | `fetch()` + DOM replace | Include panel loading |\n| `toolbut([...])` | `#toolbut` container (task 204) | 6 custom buttons |\n| `dwap.page.*` | `$.page.fn.*` | Page functions |\n| `dwap.pdata` | `$.dui.pdata` | Page data |\n| `dwap.bhave` | `$.dui.bhave` | Behaviour settings |\n| `ajaxget()` | `ajaxget()` | Shimmed, same signature |\n| `butEn()` | DEPRECATED — toolbar-plugin manages | Remove |\n\n### Dependencies\n- Task 205 (tree-component) — DUI tree plugin must exist for WO tree\n- Task 204 (toolbut-container) — custom toolbar button container\n- Task 187 (modal-plugin) — for dialog replacements"}
2026-03-03 15:23:55,383 807513 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'goal', 'text': 'FRESH migration of vwltsa/sa_jobman (Job Manager) from EUI to DUI using /dui-migrate skill.\n\n**Existing DUI files must be DELETED first** — the previous mechanical conversion (sa_jobman.pug, js/sa_jobman.js) will never work. Start clean from EUI source.\n\n## EUI Baseline Screenshots\n- `.pw/eui-sa_jobman-wide.png` — empty page, full layout (west/center split)\n- `.pw/eui-sa_jobman-loaded.png` — J-00011 loaded, Main tab, WO tree with 13 operations\n- `.pw/eui-sa_jobman-dates.png` — Dates tab (Create/Printed/Closed/Status Change + Planning fieldset)\n- `.pw/eui-sa_jobman-costing.png` — Costing tab (Estimator, Total, Cost Items, Actual Cost fieldsets)\n- `.pw/eui-sa_jobman-engineering.png` — Engineering tab (Linked Part + General fieldsets)\n- `.pw/eui-sa_jobman-seq10.png` — Operation SEQ:10 form (Status, Resource, Template, Plan Plus, Dates, Quantities, Last Modified)\n\n## Page Structure\n- West panel (250px): status filter buttons, job class filter, job combobox with nav arrows, WO tree\n- Center panel: context-sensitive tabs — changes based on tree node type:\n  - Root (Job) → Master tab → inner tabs: Main, Dates, Costing, Engineering, Attachments, User Fields, Specs, Quality\n  - Sub Assembly → Sub Assembly tab (separate include wo_sub_inc)\n  - Operation (SEQ) → Operation tab → inner tabs: Main, Setup/Run, Costing, User Fields, Specifications, Parts, Quality, Gauge\n\n## Complexity\n- 3 nested form contexts with different tab sets\n- Tree with custom formatters (progress bars, colored SEQ numbers, NCR flags, icons)\n- 6 custom toolbar buttons + 5 dialogs\n- 18 SQL endpoints\n- 3 include panels (wo_bas_inc, wo_sub_inc, wo_seq_inc)\n- Extensive page-specific CSS\n\nCRITICAL: Page-specific CSS must be preserved through migration — extract to css/sa_jobman.css, include in pug.'}
