2026-03-03 17:58:45,849 807513 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 5, 'text': '## Investigation findings (EUI vs DUI comparison)\n\n### What\'s wrong — everything about the tree is broken:\n1. **Tree not auto-expanding** — EUI expands all nodes on job select, DUI stays collapsed at root\n2. **Root node text** — EUI shows "J-00010 P/N: PPS-TEST", DUI shows just "J-00010"\n3. **Operation labels** — EUI shows "SEQ: 5", "SEQ: 10" etc, DUI shows bare numbers\n4. **Sub assembly labels** — EUI shows "SUB: 1", DUI shows bare "1"\n5. **Custom icons** — EUI has wrench/lock/checkmark/edit icons per operation state, DUI has none\n6. **Person/assignment icons** — shown on assigned operations in EUI, missing in DUI\n7. **NCR flag icons** — red flag on NCR operations in EUI, missing in DUI\n8. **Progress bars** — orange bar showing % complete in EUI, missing in DUI\n9. **Root node green highlight** — styled background in EUI, plain text in DUI\n10. **Combobox widget** — EUI has EasyUI combobox with dropdown, DUI renders native HTML `<select>`\n11. **Job Class Filters label** — "Job Class Filters (278)" with count in EUI, no label in DUI\n\n### Root causes to investigate:\n- CSS file `css/sa_jobman.css` — probably not included or stripped during migration\n- Tree formatter functions in sa_jobman.js — may have been stripped or broken\n- Tree expandAll call — may not fire after data load\n- Combobox initialization on #wosel — plugin not attaching\n\n### Approach:\n1. Read EUI sa_jobman.js tree formatter to understand what HTML it builds\n2. Read DUI sa_jobman.js to see what was preserved vs stripped\n3. Check if css/sa_jobman.css exists and is included in pug\n4. Check combobox initialization\n5. Fix each gap one at a time, verify in browser after each'}
2026-03-03 18:04:07,932 807513 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 5, 'id': 597, 'text': '## Investigation findings — ROOT CAUSE\n\n### The DUI tree plugin is architecturally different from EasyUI tree\n\n**EUI tree DOM (EasyUI):**\n```html\n<ul class="wotree tree">\n  <li>\n    <div class="tree-node droppable tree-node-selected">\n      <span class="tree-hit tree-expanded"></span>\n      <span class="tree-icon tree-folder tree-folder-open bas"></span>\n      <span class="tree-title">\n        <span>J-00010</span>\n        <span class="partid" title="PPS-TEST">PPS-TEST</span>\n      </span>\n    </div>\n    <ul style="display:block">\n      <li>\n        <div class="tree-node droppable">\n          <span class="tree-indent"></span>\n          <span class="tree-icon tree-file seq-U"></span>\n          <span class="tree-title">\n            <span class="bar" style="background-size:0% 100%">5</span>\n            <span class="opnparts-closed"></span>\n          </span>\n        </div>\n      </li>\n```\n\n**DUI tree DOM (DaisyUI tree-plugin.js):**\n```html\n<ul class="wotree mt-2">\n  <li id="J-00010">\n    <details>\n      <summary class="tree-selected">\n        <span class="tree-text">J-00010</span>\n      </summary>\n      <ul class="menu">\n        <li id="J-00010^0^5">\n          <a data-node-id="J-00010^0^5">\n            <span class="tree-text">5</span>\n          </a>\n        </li>\n```\n\n### Why everything is broken:\n\n1. **Formatter never called** — tree-plugin.js `createNodeEl()` line 88 does `textSpan.textContent = nodeData.text` — never calls `opts.formatter(node)`. The formatter function in sa_jobman.js exists but is completely ignored.\n\n2. **No .tree-icon elements** — DUI tree uses `$.dui.icon(nodeData.iconCls)` for Lucide SVG icons. EUI tree uses `<span class="tree-icon tree-file seq-U">` with CSS background-image. All custom icon classes (seq-U, seq-C, bas, sub) are dead.\n\n3. **No .tree-title elements** — DUI uses `.tree-text`. All CSS rules targeting `.tree-title` (SEQ:/SUB: labels, bar styles, NCR flags, partid) are dead.\n\n4. **No .tree-node elements** — DUI uses `<details>/<summary>` for branches, `<a>` for leaves. All CSS rules targeting `.tree-node` are dead.\n\n5. **textContent not innerHTML** — even if formatter were called, it returns HTML (`<span class="bar">5</span>`) but textContent would escape it.\n\n6. **No tree-icon class on elements** — EUI CSS uses `.tree-icon.seq-U + .tree-title::before { content: "SEQ: " }` adjacency selector. DUI has no adjacent icon element at all.\n\n### EUI CSS rules that are ALL dead in DUI:\n\n```css\n/* SEQ/SUB labels — DEAD (no .tree-icon elements) */\n.wotree .tree-icon.seq + .tree-title::before { content: "SEQ: "; }\n.wotree .tree-icon.seq-C + .tree-title::before { content: "SEQ: "; }\n.wotree .tree-icon.seq-U + .tree-title::before { content: "SEQ: "; }\n.wotree .tree-icon.seq-X + .tree-title::before { content: "SEQ: "; }\n.wotree .tree-icon.sub + .tree-title::before { content: "SUB: "; }\n\n/* Progress bars — DEAD (no .tree-title > span.bar) */\n.wotree span.tree-title span.bar { width:50px; background-size:0px 100%; background-color:#eee; background-image:url(../img/ora-0.5.png); }\n.wotree span.tree-title span.bar.grn { background-image:url(../img/grn-0.5.png); }\n\n/* Custom icons — DEAD (no .tree-icon elements) */\n.tree-icon.bas { background:url(../icons/folder_wrench.png) no-repeat; }\n.tree-icon.sub { background:url(../icons/org.png) no-repeat; }\n.tree-icon.seq-C { background:url(../icons/tick.png) no-repeat; }\n.tree-icon.seq-U { background:url(../icons/lock.png) no-repeat; }\n.tree-icon.seq-X { background:url(../icons/cross.png) no-repeat; }\n\n/* NCR, partid, opnparts — DEAD (no .tree-title parent) */\n.tree-title > .ncr { background:url(/icons/flag_red.png)... }\n.tree-title > .opnparts { background:url(/icons/part.png)... }\n.tree-title span.partid::before { content: \'P/N: \'; }\n```\n\n### What needs to happen (page-level only — plugin is FORBIDDEN to modify):\n\n**Option A: Post-process DOM in onLoadSuccess**\n- After tree loads, walk every `<span class="tree-text">` node\n- Get the stored node data via `$.data(li, \'tree-node\')`  \n- Call the formatter manually, set innerHTML instead of textContent\n- Add icon class elements or data attributes for CSS to target\n- Rewrite CSS selectors to target DUI DOM structure\n\n**Option B: Override createNodeEl before tree init**\n- Monkey-patch the tree plugin\'s createNodeEl to call formatter and use innerHTML\n- Less brittle than post-processing\n\n**Option A is safest** — stays within page-level code, doesn\'t touch plugin internals.\n\n### Additional issues beyond tree:\n- **Combobox** — #wosel renders as native `<select>`, not EasyUI combobox\n- **Tree not auto-expanding** — root `<details>` not getting `open` attribute\n- **Job Class Filters label** — "Job Class Filters (278)" missing'}
