2026-03-03 18:18:19,400 807513 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 6, 'text': '## Tree styling gaps — DUI vs EUI comparison\n\n### 1. Root node not visible / no selection highlight\n- EUI: root "J-00010 P/N: PPS-TEST" has a full-width blue highlight bar\n- DUI: root is barely visible at top — just ▼ + folder icon, no highlight\n- Fix: tree-plugin CSS needs a `.tree-selected` style with background color\n\n### 2. Vertical spacing too large — tree is not compact\n- EUI: tight line-height, nodes are ~20px apart\n- DUI: large gaps between nodes, tree takes much more vertical space\n- Fix: reduce line-height/padding on tree li/summary elements in sa_jobman.css or tree.css\n\n### 3. No tree guide lines\n- EUI: vertical/horizontal guide lines connecting parent to children\n- DUI: no lines at all — flat list appearance\n- Fix: CSS border-left on nested ul, or tree-plugin CSS for guide lines\n\n### 4. No selection highlight on click\n- EUI: clicking a node highlights it with blue bar, white text\n- DUI: `.tree-selected` class is added but no visible styling\n- Fix: add `.tree-selected` background-color rule in tree CSS or sa_jobman.css\n\n### 5. Sub-assembly children cut off\n- DUI only shows SEQ: 10-30 of SUB:1 (tree is too tall due to spacing)\n- EUI shows all 8 children (10-80) within the panel\n- Fix: once spacing is fixed, more nodes will be visible\n\n### 6. Disclosure triangles\n- EUI: custom +/- expand icons from EasyUI\n- DUI: native HTML ▼/▶ details/summary markers\n- Fix: CSS to customize the summary marker, or hide it and use a custom icon\n\n### 7. "Job Class Filters (278)" label missing\n- EUI: panel header shows "Job Class Filters ( 278 )" above the filter checkboxes\n- DUI: checkboxes are there but the panel header/title is missing\n- Fix: sa_jobman.pug needs the panel header added\n\n### Scope decision needed\nItems 1-5 are tree-plugin CSS concerns (affect ALL tree pages, not just sa_jobman).\nItems 6 is cosmetic (tree-plugin CSS).\nItem 7 is page-specific (sa_jobman.pug).\n\nShould these go on tree-component task as a new step, or stay here as page-level CSS overrides?'}
